From c96c52eb0d3a7f8844a66a2e46045069b3d823d1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lorenzo Bianconi <lorenzo@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 19:23:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 013/260] hostapd: ap: Add AFC client support

Introduce Automated Frequency Coordination (AFC) support for UNII-5 and
UNII-7 6GHz bands.
AFC client will connect to AFCD providing AP related parameter for AFC
coordinator (e.g. geolocation, supported frequencies, ..).
AFC is required for Standard Power Devices (SPDs) to determine a lists
of channels and EIRP/PSD powers that are available in the 6GHz spectrum.
AFC hostapd client is tested with AFC DUT Test Harness [0].

[0] https://github.com/Wi-FiTestSuite/AFC-DUT/tree/main

Tested-by: Felix Fietkau <nbd@nbd.name>
Tested-by: Allen Ye <allen.ye@mediatek.com>
Tested-by: Krishna Chaitanya <chaitanya.mgit@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Lorenzo Bianconi <lorenzo@kernel.org>

1. Move request id from configuration to hostapd_data, which is replaced
with a random number. It will increment for each new request.
2. Replace all json-c API with hostapd internal JSON implementation.

This commit have dependency on d38cf8ff61ef5502043c1c9d7475e0c43500d7ef
mtk: hostapd: Add afc info and send request command
We can merge the two commits together.

Signed-off-by: Allen Ye <allen.ye@mediatek.com>
